  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d3aabbc3",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Notes from exploring the data:\n",
    "- 318 rows, 20 columns\n",
    "- \"Contract_Type\" and \"Contract_Number\" and \"Shape\" are not especially relevant, can remove\n",
    "- Column name formats need to be standardized using snake_case\n",
    "- In \"System\" column, the first part of the data is just the parent ID - could remove to just consider field IDs and rename the column to \"Field_IDs\"\n",
    "- \"FeatureStatus\" column could be renamed to just \"Status\" for clarity\n",
    "- Data types for some columns can be changed \n",
    "    - JOP status data type is a checkbox object but registers has True/False, so can be kept\n",
    "    - Commission_Date should be in datetime format\n",
    "- \"Maint_By_Spec\" and \"Construction_Entity_Spec\" contain over 50% empty values\n",
    "- Only one row contains over 50% empty values\n",
    "- Duplicates by location are most likely caused by more than one turf field exisisting at the same address together, not errors in the data\n",
    "- \"Unknown\" is substituted in for null values across columns\n",
    "- Borough names are shortened to just one letter, could expand them for clarity"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f646ebce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Apply pandas data manipulation techniques to correct the noted errors:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "4b2c243d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Remove unnecessary columns\n",
    "df = df.drop(columns=[\"Contract_Type\", \n",
    "                      \"Contract_Number\", \n",
    "                      \"Shape\", \n",
    "                      \"Maint_By_Spec\", \n",
    "                      \"Construction_Entity_Spec\"])\n",
    "\n",
    "#Rename columns to relevant descriptions in snake_case\n",
    "df = df.rename(columns={\"SYSTEM\":\"Field_ID\",\n",
    "                   \"PARENTID\":\"Parent_ID\",\n",
    "                   \"DEPARTMENT\":\"Department\",\n",
    "                   \"DESCRIPTION\":\"Description\",\n",
    "                   \"Maint_By\":\"Maintained_By\",\n",
    "                   \"SYNTURF_Location\":\"Location\",\n",
    "                   \"RETIRED\":\"Retired\",\n",
    "                   \"FeatureStatus\":\"Status\"\n",
    "                   })\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "#Drop the parent_ID and \"SYNTURF\" from the Field_ID\n",
    "df[\"Field_ID\"] = df[\"Field_ID\"].str.extract(r\"(0\\d+$)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#Remove the borough information from Parent_ID\n",
    "df[\"Parent_ID\"] = df[\"Parent_ID\"].str.extract(r\"(\\d+$)\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#Change \"Commission_Date\" to datetime object\n",
    "df[\"Commission_Date\"] = pd.to_datetime(df[\"Commission_Date\"], format=\"%m/%d/%Y\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#Replace \"Unknown\" and \"Not Applicable with NaN\n",
    "df.replace([\"Unknown\", \"Not Applicable\"], pd.NA, inplace=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "#If the location contains \"&\" change it to \"and\"\n",
    "df[\"Location\"] = df[\"Location\"].replace(r\"\\s&\\s\", \" and \", regex=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "#Combine \"crumb rubber\" and \"rubber crumb\" infill material types\n",
    "df[\"Infill_Material\"] = df[\"Infill_Material\"].replace(\"Crumb Rubber\", \"Rubber Crumb\")\n",
    "\n",
    "#Expand borough names\n",
    "df[\"Borough\"] = df[\"Borough\"].replace({\"B\":\"Brooklyn\",\n",
    "                                       \"M\": \"Manhattan\",\n",
    "                                       \"Q\": \"Queens\",\n",
    "                                       \"X\": \"Bronx\",\n",
    "                                       \"R\": \"Staten Island\"})"
   ]
  },
