    "**Step 2:** Generate research questions that could be asked and answered based on the data. *What is the most important information to focus on?* What types of results should we expect to see?\n",
    "\n",
    "##### **🏈 1:** What boroughs have the most turf fields? Are they new and maintained or old?\n",
    "\n",
    "##### **🏈 2:** Who maintains most of the fields and where? Are they **active** and **accessible?**\n",
    "\n",
    "##### **🏈 3:** How many fields are located within a **Jointly Operated Playground (JOP)?** How many other fields are apart of a playground system?\n",
    "\n",
    "Start to use pandas to organize and summarize the data in response to the research questions."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cd074aad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "**Question 1:** What boroughs have the most turf fields? Are they new and maintained or old?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "36bd76bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "#Which borough has the most turf fields? \n",
    "df.groupby(\"Borough\").size() \n",
    "b_fields = df[df[\"Borough\"] == \"Brooklyn\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "#What percentage of those fields have 'infill' turf type?\n",
    "percent_infill = (b_fields[\"Turf_Type\"] == \"Infill\").sum() / b_fields.shape[0] *100\n",
    "percent_infill = round(percent_infill, 1) \n",
    "\n",
    "#What does the distribution of infill materials look like?\n",
    "materials = b_fields.groupby(\"Infill_Material\").size().drop(\"Non-Infill\").sort_values(ascending=False)\n",
    "\n",
    "#How many fields are inactive?\n",
    "percent_inactive = (b_fields[\"Status\"] != \"Active\").sum() / b_fields.shape[0] * 100\n",
    "percent_inactive = round(percent_inactive, 1) \n",
    "retired_count = b_fields[\"Retired\"].sum() \n",
    "\n",
    "#How many fields are less than 5 years old?\n",
    "newest_count = b_fields[b_fields[\"Commission_Date\"] >= \"2021-01-01\"].shape[0] \n",
    "\n",
    "#How many fields are actively maintained by a company?\n",
    "percent_maintained = b_fields[\"Maintained_By\"].notna().sum() / b_fields.shape[0] * 100\n",
    "percent_maintained = round(percent_maintained, 1) \n",
    "owners = b_fields.groupby(\"Maintained_By\").size().sort_values(ascending=False) "
   ]
